e it has been recorded from the 13th century onward.","Irish: when not of English origin (see 1 above), a surname adopted for Gaelic <b>Ó Maolfhoghmhair</b> (see   Milford  ), the name of an ecclesiastical family.","Swedish (mainly <b>Palmér</b>): ornamental name formed with <i>palm</i> ‘palm tree’ + the suffix <i>-ér</i> (a derivative of Latin <i>-erius</i>) or <i>-er</i> (from German)."],"variants":[{"name":"Milford","meanings":["English (mainly Devon): habitational name from any of the many places called Milford, deriving from Old English <i>myln</i> ‘mill’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’.","Irish (Antrim and Galway): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maolfhoghmhair</b> ‘descendant of <i>Maolgfhoghmhair</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘chief of harvest’. The Irish name was first Anglicized as <b>Mullover</b>, which was later assimilated to <i>Milford</i>. See also   Palmer  ."]},{"name":"Palmiere","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Dante, Enrico, Nicola, Salvatore, Vittorio.","Italian: from <i>palmiere</i> ‘palmer, pilgrim’. See   Palmer  ."]},{"name":"Parmer","meanings":["English: variant of   Palmer  .","Indian (northern states): variant of   Parmar  ."]},{"name":"Palmore","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Palmer   or an Americanized form of South German   Balmer  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Isabella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":11,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":20,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Mary Isabella Seddinghouse, Baroness Palmer was born in 1317, in East Preston, Sussex, England as the daughter of Sir John Seddinghouse Knight. She married Adam Palmer in 1333, in Angmering, Sussex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1380, in Sussex, England, at the age of 63, and was buried in Sussex, England."},"et":{"1317–1380":"1317–1380","1318–1371":"1318–1371","1339–1380":"1339–1380","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1337":"1337","1333":"1333","about 1339":"1339","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1371":"1371","1380":"1380","1318":"1318","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","1339":"1339","Angmering, Sussex, England":"Angmering, Sussex, England","Angmering Manor, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Angmering, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Steyning, Sussex, England":"Steyning, Sussex, England","East Preston, Sussex, England":"East Preston, Sussex, England"},"fi":{"1317–1380":"1317–1380","1318–1371":"1318–1371","1339–1380":"1339–1380","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1333":"1333","about 1339":"1339","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1371":"1371","1380":"1380","1318":"1318","1317":"1317","1328":"1328","1339":"1339","Angmering, Sussex, England":"Angmering, Sussex, England","Angmering Manor, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Angmering, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt 